['(father of Donald Payne, Jr.), a Representative from New Jersey; \r', 'born in Newark, Essex County, N.J., July 16, 1934; graduated from Barringer \r', 'High School, Newark, N.J., 1952; B.A., Seton Hall University, South Orange, \r', 'N.J., 1957; teacher; insurance executive; president, Young Men’s Christian \r', 'Association of the United States (YMCA), 1970-1973; member, Essex County, N.J., \r', 'board of chosen freeholders, 1972-1978; unsuccessful candidate for nomination \r', 'to the Ninety-seventh Congress in 1980; member of the Newark, N.J., Municipal \r', 'Council, 1982-1988; chairman, Essex county Democratic committee, 2003-2004; \r', 'unsuccessful candidate for nomination to the One Hundredth Congress in 1986; \r', 'elected as a Democrat to the One Hundred First and to the eleven succeeding \r', 'Congresses (January 3, 1989-March 6, 2012); died on March 6, 2012, in \r', 'Livingston, N.J. \r', '


\r', '

Bio: ['a Representative from Texas; born in Clarendon, Donley County, Tex., \r', 'July 15, 1958; graduated from Clarendon High School, Clarendon, Tex., 1976; \r', 'B.A., Texas Tech University, Lubbock, Tex., 1980; J.D., University of Texas \r', 'School of Law, Austin, Tex., 1983; staff, United States Representative Thomas \r', 'Gilbert Loeffler of Texas, 1983-1985; staff, United States Representative Larry \r', 'Ed Combest of Texas, 1985-1988; deputy assistant Secretary of State for \r', 'Legislative Affairs, United States Department of State, 1988-1989; rancher; \r', 'lawyer, private practice; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred Fourth and \r', 'to the eleven succeeding Congresses (January 3, 1995-present); chair, Committee \r', 'on Armed Services (One Hundred Fourteenth and One Hundred Fifteenth \r', 'Congresses).\r']

Name: TIBERI, Patrick (Pat)
Bio: ['a Representative from Ohio; born in Columbus, Franklin County, Ohio, \r', 'October 21, 1962; graduated from Northland High School, Columbus, Ohio, 1981; \r', 'B.A., Ohio State University, Columbus, Ohio, 1985; member of the Ohio state \r', 'house of representatives, 1992-2001; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred \r', 'Seventh and to the eight succeeding Congresses until his resignation on January 15, 2018 (January 3, 2001-January 15, 2018); \r', 'chair, Joint Economic Committee (One Hundred Fifteenth Congress).\r']

Name: TIERNEY, John F.
Bio: ['a Representative from Massachusetts; born in Salem, Essex County, \r', 'Mass., September 18, 1951; graduated from Salem High School, Salem, Mass.; \r', 'B.A., Salem State College, Salem, Mass., 1973; J.D., Suffolk University, \r', 'Boston, Mass., 1976; member of the Salem, Mass., chamber of commerce, \r', '1976-1996; President, Salem, Mass. chamber of commerce, 1995; trustee, Salem \r', 'State College, Salem, Mass., 1992-1997; elected as a Democrat to the One \r', 'Hundred Fifth and to the eight succeeding Congresses (January 3, 1997-January \r', '3, 2015); unsuccessful candidate for renomination to the One Hundred Fourteenth \r', 'Congress in 2014.\r']

Name: TIPTON, Scott
Bio: ['a Representative from Colorado; born in Espanola, Rio Arriba County, \r', 'N. Mex., November 9, 1956; graduated from Cortez High School; B.A., Fort Lewis \r', 'College, Durango, Colo., 1978; business owner; member of the Colorado state \r', 'house of representatives, 2008-2010; unsuccessful candidate for election to the \r', 'One Hundred Tenth Congress in 2006; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred \r', 'Twelfth and to the three succeeding Congresses (January 3, \r', '2011-present).\r']

Name: TONKO, Paul
Bio: ['a Representative from New York; born in Amsterdam, Montgomery \r', 'County, N.Y., June 18, 1949; graduated from Amsterdam High School, Amsterdam, \r', 'N.Y., 1967; B.S., Clarkson University, Potsdam, N.Y., 1971; public works \r', 'engineer; state transportation agency employee; member of the Montgomery \r', 'County, N.Y. board of supervisors, 1976-1983; chairman, Montgomery County, N.Y. \r', 'board of supervisors, 1981; member of the New York state assembly, 1983-2007; \r', 'president, New York state energy research and development authority, 2007-2008; \r', 'elected as a Democrat to the One Hundred Eleventh and to the four succeeding \r', 'Congresses (January 3, 2009-present).\r']

Name: TOWNS, Edolphus
Bio: ['a Representative from New York; born in Chadbourn, Columbus County, \r', 'N.C., July 21, 1934; graduated from West Side High School, Chadbourn, N.C., \r', '1952; B.S., North Carolina Agricultural and Technical State University, \r', 'Greensboro, N.C., 1956; M.S.W., Adelphi University, Garden City, N.Y., 1973; \r', 'United States Army, 1956-1958; teacher, Fordham University, New York, N.Y.; \r', 'deputy president, borough of Brooklyn, N.Y., 1976-1982; elected as Democrat to \r', 'the Ninety-eighth and to the fourteen succeeding Congresses (January 3, \r', '1983-January 3, 2013); chair, Committee on Oversight and Government Reform (One \r', 'Hundred Eleventh Congress); was not a candidate for reelection to the One \r', 'Hundred Thirteenth Congress in 2012.\r']

Name: TSONGAS, Nicola S. (Niki)
Bio: [' (wife of Paul Tsongas), \r', 'a Representative from Massachusetts; born in Chico, Butte County, \r', 'Calif., April 26, 1946; graduated from Narimasu American High School, Tokyo, \r', 'Japan, 1964; attended Michigan State University, East Lansing, Mich.; B.A., \r', 'Smith College, Northampton, Mass. 1968; J.D., Boston University, Boston, Mass., \r', '1988; social worker; lawyer, private practice; dean of external affairs, \r', 'Middlesex Community College, Lowell, Mass., 1997-2007; elected as a Democrat to \r', 'the One Hundred Tenth Congress, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused \r', 'by the resignation of Representative Martin Meehan, and reelected to the five \r', 'succeeding Congresses (October 16, 2007-present).\r']

Name: TURNER, Michael R.
Bio: ['a Representative from Ohio; born in Dayton, Montgomery County, Ohio, \r', 'January 11, 1960; graduated from Belmont High School, Dayton, Ohio, 1978; B.A., \r', 'Ohio Northern University, Ada, Ohio, 1982; J.D., Case Western Reserve \r', 'University, Cleveland, Ohio, 1985; M.B.A., University of Dayton, Dayton, Ohio, \r', '1992; lawyer, private practice; mayor of Dayton, Ohio, 1994-2002; elected as a \r', 'Republican to the One Hundred Eighth and to the seven succeeding Congresses \r', '(January 3, 2003-present).\r']

Name: TURNER, Robert L.
Bio: ['a Representative from New York; born in New York, New York County, \r', 'N.Y., May 2, 1941; graduated from Richmond Hill High School, Richmond Hill, \r', 'N.Y.; B.A., St. Johns University, New York, N.Y.; United States Army, \r', '1962-1964; businessman; unsuccessful candidate for election to the United \r', 'States House of Representatives in 2010; elected as a Republican to the One \r', 'Hundred Twelfth Congress, by special election to fill the vacancy caused by the \r', 'resignation of United States Representative Anthony D. Weiner (September 13, \r', '2011-January 3, 2013); not a candidate for reelection in 2012, but was an \r', 'unsuccessful candidate for nomination for the United States Senate.\r']

Name: UPTON, Frederick Stephen
Bio: ['a Representative from Michigan; born in St. Joseph, Berrien County, \r', 'Mich., April 23, 1953; graduated from Shattuck School, Fairbault, Minn.; A.B., \r', 'University of Michigan, Ann Arbor, Mich., 1975; staff, United States \r', 'Representative David Stockman of Michigan, 1976-1980; staff, United States \r', 'Office of Management and Budget, 1981-1985; elected as a Republican to the One \r', 'Hundredth and to the fifteen succeeding Congresses (January 3, 1987-present); \r', 'chair, Committee on Energy and Commerce (One Hundred Twelfth through One \r', 'Hundred Fourteenth Congresses). \r']

Name: VAN HOLLEN, Christopher
Bio: ['a Senator and a Representative from Maryland; born in Karachi, \r', 'Pakistan, January 10, 1959; B.A., Swarthmore College, Swarthmore, Pa., 1982; \r', 'M.P.P., Harvard University, Cambridge, Mass., 1985; J.D., Georgetown \r', 'University, Washington, D.C., 1990; lawyer, private practice; member of the \r', 'Maryland state house of representatives, 1990-1994; member of the Maryland \r', 'state senate, 1994-2002; elected as a Democrat to the One Hundred Eighth and to \r', 'the six succeeding Congresses (January 3, 2003-January 3, 2017); was not a \r', 'candidate for reelection to the House of Representatives but was elected as a \r', 'Democrat to the United States Senate in 2016 for the term ending January 3, \r', '2023; chair, Democratic Senatorial Campaign \r', 'Committee (2017-).\r']

Name: VELÁZQUEZ, Nydia M.
Bio: ['a Representative from New York; born in Yabucoa, P.R., March 28, \r', '1953; B.A., University of Puerto Rico, Rio Piedras, 1974; M.A., New York \r', 'University, New York, N.Y., 1976; faculty, University of Puerto Rico, Humacao, \r', 'P.R., 1976-1981; adjunct professor, Hunter College, City University of New \r', 'York, N.Y., 1981-1983; staff, United States Representative Edolphus Towns of \r', 'New York, 1983; member of the New York, N.Y., city council, 1984; national \r', 'director, Migration Division Office, Puerto Rico department of labor and human \r', 'resources, 1986-1989; director, department of Puerto Rican community affairs in \r', 'the United States for the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, 1989-1992; elected as a \r', 'Democrat to the One Hundred Third and to the twelve succeeding Congresses \r', '(January 3, 1993-present); chair, Committee on Small Business (One Hundred \r', 'Tenth and One Hundred Eleventh Congresses).\r']

Name: VISCLOSKY, Peter

Name: WALBERG, Tim
Bio: ['a Representative from Michigan; born in Chicago, Cook County, Ill., \r', 'April 12, 1951; graduated from Thornton Fractional Township North High School, \r', 'Calumet, Ill., 1969; attended Western Illinois University, Macomb, Ill., \r', '1969-1970; attended Moody Bible College Institute, Chicago, Ill., 1970-1973; \r', 'B.S., Fort Wayne Bible College, Fort Wayne., Ind., 1975; M.A., Wheaton College, \r', 'Wheaton, Ill., 1978; minister; member of the Michigan state house of \r', 'representatives, 1983-1998; unsuccessful candidate for nomination to the One \r', 'Hundred Ninth Congress in 2004; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred \r', 'Tenth Congress (January 3, 2007-January 3, 2009); unsuccessful candidate for \r', 'reelection to the One Hundred Eleventh Congress in 2008; elected as a \r', 'Republican to the One Hundred Twelfth and to the three succeeding Congresses \r', '(January 3, 2011-present).\r']

Name: WALDEN, Greg
